    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Japanese phrase translated as “grainy, blurry, and out-of-focus.” This refers to a style of photography popularized in Japan in the late 1960s, associated with Provoke magazine, and most particularly with the work of Daido Moriyama.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
